So the velocity components are constant in x (vx = v0x), and vy decreases 
linearly with time. The trajectory is a parabola.

The analytic solution for range is (v0² * sin(2θ))/g. For θ=45°, sin(90°)=1, so 
range is v0²/g.

For v0=50 m/s, range is 50^2 / 9.81 ≈ 254.84 m.

